document.title: 2020 New Jersey Student Learning Standards – Computer Science and Design Thinking

77A9849108DF40169D004B9F4C10468E.description:
Analyze how technology has contributed to or reduced inequities in local and global
communities and determine its short- and long-term effects.

EAEFF83A8BCD442E93C21D1541F22BA7.description:
Technological choices and
opportunities vary due to factors
such as differences in economic
resources, location, and cultural
values.

05C6985D7F544CB68B00AD73CE5C3004.description:
Ethics and Culture concerns the profound effects that technologies have on people, how those effects can widen or narrow disparities, and the
responsibility that people have for the societal consequences of their technological decisions.

D969C7D45E284EA89064D0A59584F3A0.description: Identify the impact of a specific technology on the environment and determine what can be done to increase positive effects and to reduce any negative effects, such as climate change.

3A8A2FDA3F9546D48CDBB65C208B33FC.description: Explain the impact that resources, such as energy and materials used to develop technology, have on the environment.

3F604E3DAFE545BBBB22DEEB7A71EE91.description: Explain why human-designed systems, products, and environments need to be constantly monitored, maintained, and improved.

7E1258C3CE9F4821B2640ADE8422F691.description: Describe ways that various technologies are used to reduce improper use of resources.

325A89F8A6C640EFBF0ED66B98B18CEC.description:
Describe how resources such as material, energy, information, time, tools, people,
and capital are used in products or systems.

4E6B4680E6A845A1AD558C4AD3440E38.description:
The technology developed
for the human designed
world can have unintended
consequences for the
environment.Technology must be continually developed and made more efficient to reduce the need for nonrenewable resources.

B5F75F35C09E4F5586F55B516A3FAAC4.description:
Many of engineering and technology’s impacts on society and the environment are widely regarded as desirable. However, other impacts are regarded
as less desirable. Effects of Technology on the Natural World concerns the positive and negative ways that technologies affect the natural world.

B94E5813545A4D77A005EA70FBCCC4A3.description: Effects of Technology on the Natural World

0FCDC44759A0455EAC87E15DF6BB4303.description: Identify how improvement in the understanding of materials science impacts technologies.

A50E89A0424C400B97E82D839BAFF652.description: Redesign an existing product for a different purpose in a collaborative team.

435C54497E2A4FAC873C755011692909.description:
Identify new technologies resulting from the demands, values, and interests of
individuals, businesses, industries, and societies.

41188DD9C06A488A95D02E1C0EE60E33.description:
Troubleshoot a product that has stopped working and brainstorm ideas to correct the
problem.

6E77498803004170A653A716FA864A24.description:
Technology innovation and
improvement may be
influenced by a variety of
factors.Engineers create and modify technologies to meet people’s needs and wants; scientists ask questions about the natural world.

3DD86D14CE284FF19B4DDB5F9E00EACF.description:
Human population, patterns and movement focus on the size, composition, distribution, and movement of human populations and how they are
fundamental and active features on Earth’s surface. This includes understanding that the expansion and redistribution of the human population affects
patterns of settlement, environmental changes, and resource use. Patterns and movements of population also relate to physical phenomena including
climate variability, landforms, and locations of various natural hazards and their effects on population size, composition, and distribution.

FCA0A8E0381E402291B3DE648F70EE7A.description:
Describe a technology/tool that has made the way people live easier or has led to a
new business or career.

2089A0A14E824106B0E1C8539790F40B.description:
Analyze the effectiveness of a new product or system and identify the positive
and/or negative consequences resulting from its use.

EB2294372C3C447D8598905B3CF5DDE6.description:
Evaluate how well a new tool has met its intended purpose and identify any
shortcomings it might have.

5734F97B414E48CB83D6791E1AA0F4A5.description:
A new tool may have
favorable or unfavorable
results as well as both
positive and negative effects
on society. Technology spurs new businesses and careers.

79BA89FDD20548D896131098955A78C0.description:
Explain how societal needs and wants influence the development and function of a
product and a system.

5FDD397E4D6B40C8BC8A16CA38766688.description:
Societal needs and wants
determine which new tools
are developed to address
real-world problems.

9D159181366244BE9EF48CF6D8D786EC.description:
Societies influence technological development. Societies are characterized by common elements such as shared values, differentiated roles, and cultural
norms, as well as by entities such as community institutions, organizations, and businesses. Interaction of Technology and Humans concerns the ways
society drives the improvement and creation of new technologies, and how technologies both serve and change society.

FDDBDA52F0464215B1F6D5D53F838FA7.description:
Evaluate and test alternative solutions to a problem using the constraints and trade-
offs identified in the design process.

CBF6CD3E2E60424DA7CC0AA95CE4416F.description: Describe how specifications and limitations impact the engineering design process.

7AC9C7EB169D478EA2737CC1702AE8E0.description:
Explain factors that influence the development and function of products and systems
(e.g., resources, criteria, desired features, constraints).

1AAF78B742C54147848B06593824E31B.description: Engineering design requirements include desired features and limitations that need to be considered.

F21522E3DDD64E54A73AE3C1CBB7F539.description:
Follow step by step directions to assemble a product or solve a problem, using
appropriate tools to accomplish the task.

B36DA00BA3114CBB93F19A724C3FB1F7.description:
Collaborate with peers to collect information, brainstorm to solve a problem, and
evaluate all possible solutions to provide the best results with supporting sketches or models.

52CA34283B91409EB55BD582668403D9.description: Explain the functions of a system and its subsystems.

2CE887CE5DD1468DAC6E6D0A2EE45FB2.description:
Engineering design is a
systematic and creative
process of communicating
and collaborating to meet a
design challenge.Often, several design solutions exist, each better in some way than the others.

173E9417D24D4ADD8A84070A81325ED7.description:
People design for enjoyment and to solve problems, extend human capabilities, satisfy needs and wants, and improve the human condition. Engineering
Design, a systematic approach to creating solutions to technological problems and finding ways to meet people’s needs and desires, allows for the
effective and efficient development of products and systems.

ACC0F1DD42CE43C8B7B40FD1E97E2813.description:
Develop programs using an iterative process, implement the program design, and test
the program to ensure it works as intended

10C97D938AEC4B54832DC6D7B5282CA6.description:
Individuals develop
programs using an iterative
process involving design,
implementation, testing, and
review.

70CB72E8F56B4046A69EAED6D4AD3EB6.description: Modify, remix, or incorporate pieces of existing programs into one’s own work to add additional features or create a new program.

8EF799E8C6F747E7996B4F47AA828F7C.description:
Break down problems into smaller, manageable sub-problems to facilitate program
development.

8B37BDAAC2FC49D9B282CE6EEB0D5CC7.description: Programs can be broken down into smaller parts to facilitate their design, implementation, and review. Programs can also be created by incorporating smaller portions of programs that already exist.

62ECD23F2C494391B5F2B608FF6CD032.description: Create programs that include sequences, events, loops, and conditionals.

2F92E038351B4E71AC7F3A7CB3395E2B.description: A variety of control structures are used to change the flow of program execution (e.g., sequences, events, loops, conditionals).

9EDFC08A0AEB4E3682BFCEC5CC833BD3.description: Create programs that use clearly named variables to store and modify data.

D213DE0631694DEB9F62ACBD7385331E.description: Programming languages provide variables, which are used to store and modify data.

343CB97CC3404E7BB535FAC70F34B3D9.description:
Compare and refine multiple algorithms for the same task and determine which is the
most appropriate.

A882805D8550436EAF8FBEF3E1DD87D6.description:
Different algorithms can
achieve the same result.Some algorithms are more appropriate for a specific use than others.

4D7361B2F76546C89B177BD96D7FBAE6.description:
An algorithm is a sequence of steps designed to accomplish a specific task. Algorithms are translated into programs, or code, to provide instructions for
computing devices. Algorithms and programming control all computing systems, empowering people to communicate with the world in new ways and
solve compelling problems.

5B40F320F00144398364077A83FEE5F1.description:
Propose cause and effect relationships, predict outcomes, or communicate ideas
using data.

0C7C7A89EA184CD291D06BEEE863EFA8.description:
Many factors influence the
accuracy of inferences and
predictions.

39BD2403DD5D4ABFBBE2C6458F980177.description: Organize and present climate change data visually to highlight relationships or support a claim.

C14CE10550A447EC9FDF2B7C7F5E0EB3.description:
Organize and present collected data visually to communicate insights gained from
different views of the data.

9CB3E78D83FD42DC95791D7EF11AD7E6.description:
Individuals can select,
organize, and transform data
into different visual
representations and
communicate insights
gained from the data.

596789BEEAA4407AA9824A866D5475DE.description: Compare the amount of storage space required for different types of data.

27E3830E99AE4F038468F395586A621A.description:
The type of data being
stored affects the storage
requirements.

AF52ABBFE2274C1581DA477CF300788A.description:
Collect, organize, and display data in order to highlight relationships or support a
claim.

9A62D6F22EAD428084E14EF01350D498.description:
Data can be organized,
displayed, and presented to
highlight relationships

0B8B93686AC94B1E87D69168AAF0FBF1.description:
Computing systems exist to process data. The amount of digital data generated in the world is rapidly expanding, so the need to process data effectively
is increasingly important. Data is collected and stored so that it can be analyzed to better understand the world and make more accurate predictions.

900DFE4EE34C4A9FB678DEE6209E57C4.description:
Identify possible ways to improve the accessibility and usability of computing
technologies to address the diverse needs and wants of users.

1E7D6614A3494B6287DD721575FEF3AE.description:
Identify computing technologies that have impacted how individuals live and work
and describe the factors that influenced the changes.

84F4B25F9DED461F960974190E51E37E.description:
The development and
modification of computing
technology is driven by people’s
needs and wants and can affect
individuals differently.

31D0F19351574984BA685C01C52717E4.description:
Computing affects many aspects of the world in both positive and negative ways at local, national, and global levels. Individuals and communities
influence computing through their behaviors and cultural and social interactions, and, in turn, computing influences new cultural practices.

5A18320BB44E4ACA8FF59CBBF516BD28.description:
Describe physical and digital security measures for protecting sensitive personal
information.

91F3933F03F14A59A0425B618FBEE041.description:
Distinguishing between
public and private
information is important for
safe and secure online
interactions.Information can be protected using various security measures (i.e., physical and digital).

A2DC36D0225540F9B2592483A9DD564B.description:
Develop models that successfully transmit and receive information using both wired
and wireless methods.

C2772E09F6174171B50B9E0E29A87F51.description:
Information needs a physical
or wireless path to travel to
be sent and received.

A4335F184AAA4CA392AA1F0A42BA16A9.description:
Computing devices typically do not operate in isolation. Networks connect computing devices to share information and resources and are an
increasingly integral part of computing. Networks and communication systems provide greater connectivity in the computing world.

D43F1AEEC335405E9439B7C5239D2D71.description:
Identify potential solutions for simple hardware and software problems using
common troubleshooting strategies.

F00F1B5AE1FC4857A96A2472705DE973.description:
Shared features allow for
common troubleshooting
strategies that can be
effective for many systems.

FBDEA34E7C8B41C9BFBD71C87E08B237.description:
Model how computer software and hardware work together as a system to
accomplish tasks.

6596FB6249884CCF8DF2055EE625969C.description:
Software and hardware
work together as a system to
accomplish tasks (e.g.,
sending, receiving,
processing, and storing units
of information).

5E5AC1CEDB5E4A8C94FE4129DA814422.description: Model how computing devices connect to other components to form a system.

8F0AA857F8E240EBB8A81947A2D0A866.description:
Computing devices may be
connected to other devices
to form a system as a way to
extend their capabilities.

4D1C651B189E4FBDB877232E74312E0A.description:
People interact with a wide variety of computing devices that collect, store, analyze, and act upon information in ways that can affect human
capabilities both positively and negatively. The physical components (hardware) and instructions (software) that make up a computing system
communicate and process information in digital form.
